<subSubSection id="A9B0AA1421F364B0F85FBAD30F6C5F2E" pageId="0" pageNumber="62736" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="EA237A53F221DF9AE9EB265217861202" pageId="0" pageNumber="62736">Diagnosis</paragraph>
<paragraph id="9B3DDA2C4FE679512DC1E5E15C9FD9E9" pageId="0" pageNumber="62736">
(
<bibRefCitation id="2508121F888D773D6331E3E3EF011CBC" author="Silva, Jonathas Barreto Pessoa" journalOrPublisher="Universidade Federal da Parai-ba, Joao Pessoa" pageId="0" pageNumber="62736" refId="B6426797" refString="Smithsonian-Marine-Station-at-Fort-Pierce Brachidontes exustus. Smithsonian Institution https://naturalhistory2.si.edu/smsfp/irlspec/Brachidontes_exustus.htm 2020-12-12T00:00:00+02:00" year="2011">Smithsonian-Marine-Station-at-Fort-Pierce 2020</bibRefCitation>
): Shell dark-brown colour. Fan-shaped shell with fine divercating radial ribs. The ribbed surface of the shell is most evident at the outer edges. Umbones situated in the anterior end (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="AA1246DC2AFE1DDDA1BACB7046F36260" captionStartId="F6446199" pageId="0" pageNumber="62736">8</figureCitation>
<figureCitation id="AF2185F2C9F8068BE2CEA69D3BEC6C45" captionStartId="F6446206" pageId="0" pageNumber="62736">c</figureCitation>
). The interior has purple-brown blotches with one to four small purplish dysodont hinge teeth.
</paragraph>
